circumstances:
The airplane departed RAF Stradishall at 2210LT on May 8 on an operation to Hamburg. While passing over the Netherlands, it was shot down by a German fighter and crashed in Anna Paulowna, southeast of Den Helder. All six crew members were killed. 
Crew:
S/L Frank Leslie Herbert Eddison, pilot, 
P/O Norman Mervyn Kebbell Kirkcaldie, pilot, 
Sgt John Holt, observer, 
Sgt Kennedy Tait, wireless operator, 
Sgt Arnot Flaws Wilson, wireless operator, 
Sgt Cyril Paton, air gunner.
probable_cause: Shot down by a German fighter.
